aa(lp142
VI also have been touched
p143
aVby the dark side of power and leadership.
p144
aVAnd I have learned that power,
p145
aVparticularly in its absolute form,
p146
aVis an equal opportunity provider.
p147
aVIn 1986, I moved to Rwanda,
p148
aVand I worked with a very small group of Rwandan women
p149
aVto start that country's first microfinance bank.
p150
aVAnd one of the women was Agnes \u2014
p151
aVthere on your extreme left \u2014
p152
aVshe was one of the first three
p153
aVwomen parliamentarians in Rwanda,
p154
aVand her legacy should have been
p155
aVto be one of the mothers of Rwanda.
p156
aVWe built this institution based on social justice,
p157
aVgender equity,
p158
aVthis idea of empowering women.
p159
aa(lp160
VBut Agnes cared more about the trappings of power
p161
aVthan she did principle at the end.
p162
aVAnd though she had been part of building a liberal party,
p163
aVa political party
p164
aVthat was focused on diversity and tolerance,
p165
aVabout three months before the genocide, she switched parties
p166
aVand joined the extremist party, Hutu Power,
p167
aVand she became the Minister of Justice
p168
aVunder the genocide regime
p169
aVand was known for inciting men to kill faster
p170
aVand stop behaving like women.
p171
aVShe was convicted
p172
aVof category one crimes of genocide.
p173
aVAnd I would visit her in the prisons,
p174
aVsitting side-by-side, knees touching,
p175
aVand I would have to admit to myself
p176
aVthat monsters exist in all of us,
p177
aVbut that maybe it's not monsters so much,
p178
aVbut the broken parts of ourselves,
p179
aVsadnesses, secret shame,
p180
aVand that ultimately it's easy for demagogues
p181
aVto prey on those parts,
p182
aVthose fragments, if you will,
p183
aVand to make us look at other beings, human beings,
p184
aVas lesser than ourselves \u2014
p185
aVand in the extreme, to do terrible things.
p186
aa(lp187
VAnd there is no group
p188
aVmore vulnerable to those kinds of manipulations
p189
aVthan young men.
p190
aVI've heard it said that the most dangerous animal on the planet
p191
aVis the adolescent male.
p192
aVAnd so in a gathering
p193
aVwhere we're focused on women,
p194
aVwhile it is so critical that we invest in our girls
p195
aVand we even the playing field
p196
aVand we find ways to honor them,
p197
aVwe have to remember that the girls and the women
p198
aVare most isolated and violated
p199
aVand victimized and made invisible
p200
aVin those very societies
p201
aVwhere our men and our boys
p202
aVfeel disempowered,
p203
aVunable to provide.
p204
aVAnd that, when they sit on those street corners
p205
aVand all they can think of in the future
p206
aVis no job, no education,
p207
aVno possibility,
p208
aVwell then it's easy to understand
p209
aVhow the greatest source of status
p210
aVcan come from a uniform
p211
aVand a gun.
